<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900731-0118</DOCNO><DOCID>900731-0118.</DOCID><HL>   Financing Business:   Verit Industries</HL><DATE>07/31/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C21</SO><CO>   VER</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   VERIT INDUSTRIES, a real estate concern, said it completedthe private sale of 61,500 shares of a new Series Bconvertible preferred stock to a Liechtenstein investmentcompany for $15.4 million. A spokesman for Verit, based inPhoenix, Ariz., declined to identify the purchaser. Veritsaid it used $14.7 million from the sale proceeds to buy a67% interest in Touristic Club International AG Vaduz, aleisure company, which has as its principal asset the HotelViking, a resort hotel in southern Portugal. Each Series Bpreferred share is convertible into 100 Verit common shares.The purchaser agreed to vote its shares in the same manner asVerit's management for five years. The agreement also placesa limit on the number of common shares that the purchaser maysell in any 12-month period for five years. Verit is involvedin real estate development in California and Texas.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>